            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42265",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I am not sure where to start here.\r\n\r\nGenerally, if you want to add vendor specific functionality to an adapter, you'd extend the actual adapter.  So, Your_Db_Adapter_Mysqli would extends Zend_Db_Adapter_Mysqli and you'd instantiate that type.  What you are asking for here is not possible in PHP (or Java, or any language that follows a multiple interface, single inheritance class\/type\/object model).\r\n\r\nIn ZF 2.0, there will be a \"plugin\" architecture where you'll be able to hook into events that happen at specific times, for example pre-query and post-query time.\r\n\r\nMy question to you is this: what do you need the abstract adapter to do that it currently does not do?  And, is the functionality you are seeking within the domain of the problem that the Adapter is attempting to solve?\r\n\r\nI am inclined to close as not-an-issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-09-16T14:01:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-09-16T14:01:48.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
